---
title: Naive Proof Engine
---
flowchart TD
    A[prove_with_cancel sequent options] --> B{engine}
    B -->|Naive| C[naive run]
    C --> D[Create fresh BranchState]
    D --> E[Set steps_taken to 0]
    E --> F[backwards_search at depth 0]

    subgraph K[Shared backwards_search kernel]
        F --> G{cancel requested?}
        G -->|yes| X[Return Cancelled]
        G -->|no| H{deadline reached?}
        H -->|yes| Y[Return Timeout]
        H -->|no| I{depth exceeds max_depth?}
        I -->|yes| Z[Return Unknown MaxDepthExceeded]
        I -->|no| J{steps exceed max_steps?}
        J -->|yes| AA[Return Unknown MaxStepsExceeded]
        J -->|no| L[Increment steps_taken]
        L --> M[Find applicable rules]
        M --> N[Naive scheduler first non-empty priority group]
        N --> N1[1 Closing Id TopR BottomL]
        N --> N2[2 Non-branching AndL OrR ImpliesR NotL NotR ForAllR ExistsL]
        N --> N3[3 Branching AndR OrL ImpliesL]
        N --> N4[4 Reusable quantifiers ForAllL ExistsR]
        N4 --> N5[Try unused visible terms then one fresh fallback if budget remains]
        N --> O{schedule result}
        O -->|NoRules| P[Return NotProvable]
        O -->|QuantifierExhausted| Q[Return Unknown QuantifierBudgetExceeded]
        O -->|Rules| R[Try scheduled rules in order]
        R --> S[Clone BranchState for candidate]
        S --> T[Apply rule and update quantifier state if needed]
        T --> U{application result}
        U -->|Closed| V[Return Provable]
        U -->|Premises| W[Prove each premise left to right]
        W --> F
        U -->|NotImplemented or Error| AB[Merge into best failure]
        W -->|all premises provable| V
        W -->|first non-provable outcome| AC[Merge or return if Timeout or Cancelled]
        AB --> AD{more scheduled rules?}
        AC --> AD
        AD -->|yes| R
        AD -->|no| AE[Return best merged outcome]
    end
